webpackJsonp([0x7487726b91e6],{477:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>Badges are emblematic awards you can receive when you meet certain criteria or achieve events. Once received, these badges are publicly show-cased on your profile page to show your accomplishments and skills. See: hackerone.com/[hacker-name]/badges. </p>\n<p>All badges are represented by different images of bugs. Some badges have many levels depending on different criteria. These levels are represented by stars on the badge.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/badges-1-f9a734abbf035367029930ff121532f7-48010.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 204px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 108.33333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="badges-1"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/badges-1-f9a734abbf035367029930ff121532f7-48010.png"\n        srcset="/static/badges-1-f9a734abbf035367029930ff121532f7-d9a4c.png 125w,\n/static/badges-1-f9a734abbf035367029930ff121532f7-1ea23.png 250w,\n/static/badges-1-f9a734abbf035367029930ff121532f7-48010.png 408w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 204px) 100vw, 204px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>When you receive a badge for your profile page, each badge is composed of: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>The name of the badge</li>\n<li>A short description of what the badge is about</li>\n<li>The date you achieved the badge</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/badges-2-1ea72a9792ad90a179650d086ec185ab-615e1.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 208px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 105.28846153846155%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="badges-2"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/badges-2-1ea72a9792ad90a179650d086ec185ab-615e1.png"\n        srcset="/static/badges-2-1ea72a9792ad90a179650d086ec185ab-2aa81.png 125w,\n/static/badges-2-1ea72a9792ad90a179650d086ec185ab-2514d.png 250w,\n/static/badges-2-1ea72a9792ad90a179650d086ec185ab-615e1.png 416w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 208px) 100vw, 208px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/badges-3-06d7c2103ce202bedeb06b1ea24625dc-96785.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 205px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 107.8048780487805%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="badges-3"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/badges-3-06d7c2103ce202bedeb06b1ea24625dc-96785.png"\n        srcset="/static/badges-3-06d7c2103ce202bedeb06b1ea24625dc-6d52f.png 125w,\n/static/badges-3-06d7c2103ce202bedeb06b1ea24625dc-00b10.png 250w,\n/static/badges-3-06d7c2103ce202bedeb06b1ea24625dc-96785.png 410w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 205px) 100vw, 205px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<hr>\n<p>The following lists all of the current badges with a description of how to receive them: </p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Badge</th>\n<th>Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Badger</td>\n<td>Made a badge suggestion that was implemented by HackerOne</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Belle Of The Ball</td>\n<td>Submitted the top ranked report on the Hacktivity feed</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Bounty Hunter</td>\n<td>1, 10, or 100 bounties received.\n<br>\n<i>\nThere are multiple stages of this badge. You receive this badge whenever you receive 1, 10, and 100 bounties.\n</i></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Champ</td>\n<td>Received when you get 1st, 2nd, or 3rd place on a quarterly leaderboard</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Coinage</td>\n<td>Submitted a valid report during a HackerOne hackathon</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cryptolestes</td>\n<td>Solved a HackerOne Capture The Flag challenge</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Diversity</td>\n<td>Reported bugs to 5, 20, or 50 different teams.\n<br>\n<i>\nThere are multiple stages of this badge. You receive a level of this badge whenever you report bugs to 5, 20, and 50 different teams.\n</i></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Good Samaritan</td>\n<td>Resolved a report with a team that doesn\'t pay bounties</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Greybeard</td>\n<td>Submitted valid reports in 3, 6, or 12 months in a row.\n<br>\n<i>\nThere are multiple stages of this badge. You receive a level of this badge whenever you submit valid reports in 3, 6, and 12 months in a row.\n</i></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hack The World Badass</td>\n<td>Reported 10, 20, or 50 valid issues during Hack the World.\n<br>\n<i>\nThere are multiple stages of this badge. You receive a level of this badge whenever you submit 10, 20, and 50 valid reports.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hacking Hackers</td>\n<td>Hacked HackerOne</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Happy Feat</td>\n<td>Suggested a feature that was implemented on HackerOne</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Insecticide</td>\n<td>1, 50, or 500 reports closed as resolved.\n<br>\n<i>\nThere are multiple stages of this badge. You receive a level of this badge when 1, 50, and 500 reports are closed as resolved.\n</i></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>On Fire</td>\n<td>Reported 10, 15, or 20 valid issues in a row during Hack the World.\n<br>\n<i>\nThere are multiple stages of this badge. You receive this badge whenever you report 10, 15, or 20 valid issues in a row.\n</i></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Patient</td>\n<td>Waited more than six months for a report to get resolved</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Publish Or Perish</td>\n<td>Publicly disclosed a report</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Skills</td>\n<td>Got 1, 3, and 5 or more verified skills.\n<br>\n<i>\nThere are multiple stages of this badge. You receive a level of this badge when you have 1, 3, and 5 or more verified skills.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Spooky</td>\n<td>Submitted a valid report to the DoD</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Streaker</td>\n<td>Received when 2, 5, or 10 reports in a row were closed as resolved.\n<br>\n<i>\nThere are multiple stages of this badge. You receive this badge when 2, 5, or 10 reports are closed or resolved in a row.\n</i></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Swagger</td>\n<td>Received swag for the first time</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Trailblazer</td>\n<td>Was the first of multiple reporters to report a vulnerability</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Keep in mind that some badges are event-based.  </p>',frontmatter:{title:"Badges",id:"hackers/badges",path:"/hackers/badges.html",description:null}}},pathContext:{}}}});
